eading. The results of the assessment, in conjunction with a student''s academic background, goals and interests, are used by academic advisors to determine a student''s initial course selection during the first few sessions of study. Placement tests are "pass" or "fail". However, it is very important that students do their best on these tests so Edmonton University has an accurate measure of a student''s academic skills.\r\n\r\nStudents who score below 80 on the English placement examination or below 57 on the mathematics placement examination are required to take transitional coursework to increase their level of preparation for University-level courses.', 'requirements', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '14-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-18 17:25:58', '2016-08-18 17:25:58', '', 14, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/2016/08/18/14-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(76, 1, '2016-08-18 17:27:44', '2016-08-18 17:27:44', 'Transfer credits are considered from the following sources\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Credits awarded by a regionally or nationally accredited college or university recognized by the US Department of Education.</li>\r\n 	<li>Satisfactory scores on nationally recognized college equivalency examinations.</li>\r\n 	<li>Completion of non-scholastic courses evaluated by the American Council on Education (ACE).</li>\r\n 	<li>Military training as evaluated by ACE/PONSI.</li>\r\n 	<li>Credit awarded for experiential learning as documented by portfolio and evaluated for college credit by an accredited institution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease note that courses completed more than 10 years ago may not be transferable to Edmonton University programs. Students wishing to transfer credit from foreign institutions must have their transcripts assessed in English by an outside evaluator at their own expense.', 'transfer credits', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-18 17:27:44', '2016-08-18 17:27:44', '', 16, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/2016/08/18/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
