(227, 1, '2016-08-20 07:32:33', '2016-08-20 07:32:33', '', 'Centennial-College-School-of-Hospitality-Culture-and-Tourism_05-1500x630', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'centennial-college-school-of-hospitality-culture-and-tourism_05-1500x630', '', '', '2016-08-20 07:32:33', '2016-08-20 07:32:33', '', 40, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Centennial-College-School-of-Hospitality-Culture-and-Tourism_05-1500x630.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(228, 1, '2016-08-20 07:32:42', '2016-08-20 07:32:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The School of Hospitality has developed a unique relationship with the city of Boston and employers who make up the industry. The area''s many hotels and restaurants provide students with numerous opportunities for internships to satisfy the work experience requirements of their hospitality degree, including an international experience. Hospitality executives participate as guest lecturers, adjunct faculty members, student mentors, and serve on the School''s Advisory Board whose purpose is to provide the School with strategic advice and resources.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-227" src="http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Centennial-College-School-of-Hospitality-Culture-and-Tourism_05-1500x630.jpg" alt="Centennial-College-School-of-Hospitality-Culture-and-Tourism_05-1500x630" width="600" height="250" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Students receive a solid background in liberal arts and specialize in topics and courses related to the hospitality industry. The broad range of the curriculum allows students to develop a comprehensive understanding of the complex human and physical systems that make up the hospitality industry.</p>', 'school of hospitality', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-20 07:32:42', '2016-08-20 07:32:42', '', 40, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/2016/08/20/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2016-08-20 07:33:15', '2016-08-20 07:33:15', '', 'studentsoncomputer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'studentsoncomputer', '', '', '2016-08-20 07:33:15', '2016-08-20 07:33:15', '', 42, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/studentsoncomputer.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(230, 1, '2016-08-20 07:33:21', '2016-08-20 07:33:21', 'School of Information Technology is a relevant, innovative and responsive place to create, advance, transmit, and apply information technology knowledge as an enabling technology to make things happen.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-229" src="http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/studentsoncomputer.jpg" alt="studentsoncomputer" width="600" height="250" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur goal is to build a School that students want to come; that staff want to work with; and that is one of the best in teaching and research.\r\n\r\nInformation technology is an enabling technology and is one of the driving forces for the progress of the economy and society; but information technology alone will not go far enough. The future of information technology is to combine with various disciplines to produce "killer applications" that will improve the performance of these disciplines and at the meantime, to open new doors for new demand and requirements for information technology research and development.\r\n\r\nStrong links with industry and professional associations, coupled with curricula that nurture creative thinking and problem solving, helps to prepare the School''s graduates for productive careers in rapidly evolving areas of Information Technology.\r\n\r\nStrong links with industry and professional associations, coupled with curricula that nurture creative thinking and problem solving, helps to prepare the School''s graduates for productive careers in rapidly evolving areas of Information Technology.', 'school of information technology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '42-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-20 07:33:21', '2016-08-20 07:33:21', '', 42, 'http://kenningtonuniversity.co.uk/2016/08/20/42-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
